Toolbox: OFIP

Title: OFIP

Summary: OpenCv functions implementation through scilab

Version: 1.3

Author: Scilab Enterprises

Maintainer: Rishubh Jain

Category: Image Processing

Entity: Scilab Enterprises

WebSite: http://www.scilab.org

License: BSD

ScilabVersion: >= 5.4

Depends: 

Date: 2015-14-03

Description: Helps User to Use OpenCv functions in scilab
 
-install scilab
-copy paste the toolbox in contrib folder((OFIP))
-install PIMS in SCILAB
-run the builder file builder.sce
-run the loader file loader.sce
-call the cv_imread functions


Requirements: 
1) PIMS in scilab (atomsInstall("PIMS"))
2) Python 2.7 in users distribution
3) opencv installed and configured with python (sudo apt-get install python-opencv) 
4) install Numpy(for future use)
